fa7ca276c467f57adde42f80b25f1973629d2146.text_content: To all our readers,Please don’t scroll past this. This Wednesday, for the 1st time recently, we interrupt your reading to humbly ask you to support Wikipedia’s independence. Only 2% of our readers give. Many think they’ll give later, but then forget. If you are an exceptional reader who has already donated, we sincerely thank you.

If everyone reading this donated $2.75, we could keep Wikipedia thriving for years. The price of a cup of coffee is all we need. One donation may seem small, but when millions of readers each give, we can do great things.
We’re a nonprofit, and the 58 million articles that compose Wikipedia are free. Without reader contributions, big or small, we couldn’t run Wikipedia the way we do.
